#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.19:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Sīhanādavagga"
msgstr "2. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Devatāsutta"
msgstr "19. A Deity"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.19:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Imañca, bhikkhave, rattiṃ sambahulā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā "
"abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, "
"bhikkhave, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, tonight, several glorious deities, lighting up the entire Jeta’"
"s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, and said to me."

msgctxt "an9.19:1.2"
msgid "‘upasaṅkamiṃsu no, bhante, pubbe manussabhūtānaṃ pabbajitā agārāni."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, formerly when we were human beings, renunciates came to our homes."

msgctxt "an9.19:1.3"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, bhante, paccuṭṭhimha, no ca kho abhivādimha."
msgstr "We politely rose for them, but we didn’t bow."

msgctxt "an9.19:1.4"
msgid ""
"Tā mayaṃ, bhante, aparipuṇṇakammantā vippaṭisāriniyo paccānutāpiniyo hīnaṃ "
"kāyaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, having not fulfilled our duty, full of remorse and regret, we were "
"reborn in a lesser realm.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.391"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.19:2.1"
msgid "Aparāpi maṃ, bhikkhave, sambahulā devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then several other deities came to me and said:"

msgctxt "an9.19:2.2"
msgid "‘upasaṅkamiṃsu no, bhante, pubbe manussabhūtānaṃ pabbajitā agārāni."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, formerly when we were human beings, renunciates came to our homes."

#. VAR: paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha → paccuṭṭhimha ca abhivādimha ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "an9.19:2.3"
msgid "Te mayaṃ, bhante, paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha, no ca tesaṃ āsanaṃ adamha."
msgstr "We politely rose for them and bowed, but we didn’t offer a seat."

msgctxt "an9.19:2.4"
msgid ""
"Tā mayaṃ, bhante, aparipuṇṇakammantā vippaṭisāriniyo paccānutāpiniyo hīnaṃ "
"kāyaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, having not fulfilled our duty, full of remorse and regret, we were "
"reborn in a lesser realm.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.19:3.1"
msgid "Aparāpi maṃ, bhikkhave, sambahulā devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then several other deities came to me and said:"

msgctxt "an9.19:3.2"
msgid "‘upasaṅkamiṃsu no, bhante, pubbe manussabhūtānaṃ pabbajitā agārāni."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, formerly when we were human beings, renunciates came to our homes."

#. VAR: paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha → paccuṭṭhimha ca abhivādimha ca (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: āsanaṃ → āsanañca (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.19:3.3"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ, bhante, paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha āsanaṃ adamha, no ca kho "
"yathāsatti yathābalaṃ saṃvibhajimha … pe …"
msgstr ""
"We politely rose for them, bowed, and offered a seat, but we didn’t share as "
"best we could. …’"

#. VAR: yathābalaṃ → yathābalaṃ ca (?)
msgctxt "an9.19:3.4"
msgid ""
"yathāsatti yathābalaṃ saṃvibhajimha, no ca kho upanisīdimha dhammassavanāya …"
" pe …"
msgstr "‘We didn’t sit nearby to listen to the teachings. …’"

#. VAR: upanisīdimha → upanisīdimha ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "an9.19:3.5"
msgid ""
"upanisīdimha dhammassavanāya, no ca kho ohitasotā dhammaṃ suṇimha … pe …"
msgstr "‘We didn’t lend an ear to the teachings. …’"

msgctxt "an9.19:3.6"
msgid "ohitasotā ca dhammaṃ suṇimha, no ca kho sutvā dhammaṃ dhārayimha … pe …"
msgstr "‘We didn’t memorize the teachings. …’"

msgctxt "an9.19:3.7"
msgid ""
"sutvā ca dhammaṃ dhārayimha, no ca kho dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ "
"upaparikkhimha … pe …"
msgstr "‘We didn’t examine the meaning of teachings we’d memorized. …’"

msgctxt "an9.19:3.8"
msgid ""
"dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhimha, no ca kho atthamaññāya "
"dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjimha."
msgstr ""
"‘Having understood the meaning and the teaching, we didn’t practice "
"accordingly."

msgctxt "an9.19:3.9"
msgid ""
"Tā mayaṃ, bhante, aparipuṇṇakammantā vippaṭisāriniyo paccānutāpiniyo hīnaṃ "
"kāyaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, having not fulfilled our duty, full of remorse and regret, we were "
"reborn in a lesser realm.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.392"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.19:4.1"
msgid "Aparāpi maṃ, bhikkhave, sambahulā devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then several other deities came to me and said:"

msgctxt "an9.19:4.2"
msgid "‘upasaṅkamiṃsu no, bhante, pubbe manussabhūtānaṃ pabbajitā agārāni."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, formerly when we were human beings, renunciates came to our homes."

#. VAR: paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha → paccuṭṭhimha ca abhivādimha ca (s1-3)
#. VAR: āsanaṃ → āsanañca (s1-3)
#. VAR: yathābalaṃ → yathābalaṃ ca (?)
#. VAR: upanisīdimha → upanisīdimha ca (s1-3)
#. VAR: dhammānudhammaṃ → dhammānudhamma (pts1) | dhammānudhammañca (?)
msgctxt "an9.19:4.3"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ, bhante, paccuṭṭhimha abhivādimha, āsanaṃ adamha, yathāsatti "
"yathābalaṃ saṃvibhajimha, upanisīdimha dhammassavanāya, ohitasotā ca dhammaṃ "
"suṇimha, sutvā ca dhammaṃ dhārayimha, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthaṃ "
"upaparikkhimha, atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjimha."
msgstr ""
"We politely rose, bowed, and offered them a seat. We shared as best we "
"could. We sat near by to listen to the teachings, leant an ear, memorized "
"them, and examined their meaning. Understanding the teaching and the meaning "
"we practiced accordingly."

msgctxt "an9.19:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tā mayaṃ, bhante, paripuṇṇakammantā avippaṭisāriniyo apaccānutāpiniyo "
"paṇītaṃ kāyaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, having fulfilled our duty, free of remorse and regret, we were "
"reborn in a superior realm.’"

msgctxt "an9.19:4.5"
msgid ""
"Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā "
"pamādattha, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha seyyathāpi tā purimikā "
"devatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice "
"absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later, like "
"those former deities.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.19:4.6"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
